<div data-controller="object_creation_options_modal" data-modal-allow-background-close="false">
   <a href="#"
      data-action="click->object_creation_options_modal#open"
      class="text-white bg-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-800 focus:ring-4 focus:outline-none focus:ring-blue-300 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm px-5 py-2.5 text-center mr-3 md:mr-0 dark:bg-blue-600 dark:hover:bg-blue-700 dark:focus:ring-blue-800">
     <span>Create new Class</span>
   </a>

   <!-- Modal Container -->
   <div data-object_creation_options_modal-target="container"
        data-action="click->object_creation_options_modal#closeBackground keyup@window->object_creation_options_modal#closeWithKeyboard"
        class="hidden animated fadeIn fixed inset-0 overflow-y-auto flex items-center justify-center" style="z-index: 9999;">

     <div id="pick-object-type-large-modal" class="">
       <div class="relative w-full max-w-5xl max-h-full">
         <!-- Modal content -->
         <div class="relative bg-white rounded-lg shadow dark:bg-gray-700">
           <!-- Modal header -->
           <div class="flex items-center justify-between p-5 border-b rounded-t dark:border-gray-600">
             <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
               Pick type of the Class for creation
             </h3>
             <button type="button" class="text-gray-400 bg-transparent hover:bg-gray-200 hover:text-gray-900 rounded-lg text-sm p-1.5 ml-auto inline-flex items-center dark:hover:bg-gray-600 dark:hover:text-white" data-modal-hide="large-modal">
               <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
               <span class="sr-only">Close modal</span>
             </button>
           </div>
           <!-- Modal body -->
           <div class="p-6 space-y-6">
             <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
               On this page you can select which type of object you would like to create.
               Class is a toolbox with organized methodoliges by it's object. Each type of class has it's own benefits for specific usage.
               If you picked wrong class type you will be able to change one type of class on another.
             </p>

             <hr class="w-48 h-1 mx-auto my-4 bg-gray-100 border-0 rounded md:my-10 dark:bg-gray-700">
             <!-- Container -->
             <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-4">
               <!-- Grid wrapper -->
               <div class="-mx-4 flex flex-wrap">
                 <!-- Grid column -->
                 <div class="w-full flex flex-col p-4 sm:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3">
                   <!-- Column contents -->
                   <div
                     class="flex flex-col flex-1 px-10 py-12 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg"
                   >
                     <div class="flex-1">
                       <h2 class="text-gray-900 text-2xl font-bold leading-snug">
                         Class for Decision Process object
                       </h2>
                       <p class="mt-2 text-base">
                        Class for Process object its an class which built around method or algorithm.
                        If you have method or algorithm for which you want to track progress, check yourseelf,
                         estimate how much was done, validate process - this is right choice.
                       </p>
                     </div>
                     <%= link_to "Create new class for Decision process object",
                                 new_simple_class_simple_class_path(class_type: "decision_process_object_class"),
                                 class: "mt-6 inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-white font-semibold bg-blue-700 rounded-md shadow-sm" %>
                   </div>
                 </div>

                 <!-- Grid column -->
                 <div class="w-full flex flex-col p-4 sm:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3">
                   <!-- Column contents -->
                   <div
                     class="flex flex-col flex-1 px-10 py-12 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg"
                   >
                     <div class="flex-1">
                       <h2 class="text-gray-900 text-2xl font-bold leading-snug">
                         Class for Decision object
                       </h2>
                       <p class="mt-2 text-base">
                         Class for Decision object is's an class wich build for specific type of decision.
                         You will be able define method of how to make decision
                         and then grow methdologies around how to validate decisiion, estimate it's state, update decision to new fresh version and etc
                       </p>
                     </div>
                     <%= link_to "Create new class for decision object",
                                 new_simple_class_simple_class_path(class_type: "decision_object_class"),
                                 class: "mt-6 inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-white font-semibold bg-blue-700 rounded-md shadow-sm" %>
                   </div>
                 </div>




                 <!-- Grid column -->
                 <div class="w-full flex flex-col p-4 sm:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3">
                   <!-- Column contents -->
                   <div
                     class="flex flex-col flex-1 px-10 py-12 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg"
                   >
                     <div class="flex-1">
                       <h2 class="text-gray-900 text-2xl font-bold leading-snug">
                         Decision Object Container
                       </h2>
                       <p class="mt-2 text-base">
                         I've been using Tailwind CSS professionally almost every day for
                         nearly two years. Here I share some of the benefits I've gained by
                         using Tailwind.
                       </p>
                     </div>
                     <%= link_to "Create new class for decision object container",
                                 new_simple_class_simple_class_path(class_type: "decision_object_container_class"),
                                 class: "mt-6 inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-white font-semibold bg-blue-700 rounded-md shadow-sm" %>
                   </div>
                 </div>
               </div>
             </div>



           </div>
           <!-- Modal footer -->
           <div class="flex items-center p-6 space-x-2 border-t border-gray-200 rounded-b dark:border-gray-600">
             <button data-modal-hide="large-modal" type="button" class="text-white bg-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-800 focus:ring-4 focus:outline-none focus:ring-blue-300 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm px-5 py-2.5 text-center dark:bg-blue-600 dark:hover:bg-blue-700 dark:focus:ring-blue-800">I accept</button>
             <button data-modal-hide="large-modal" type="button" class="text-gray-500 bg-white hover:bg-gray-100 focus:ring-4 focus:outline-none focus:ring-gray-200 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 text-sm font-medium px-5 py-2.5 hover:text-gray-900 focus:z-10 dark:bg-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 dark:border-gray-500 dark:hover:text-white dark:hover:bg-gray-600 dark:focus:ring-gray-600">Decline</button>
           </div>
         </div>
       </div>
     </div>

   </div>
 </div>